      {
        "type": "p",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Start by obtaining API credentials and setting up the client library. Use environment variables for secure storage of API keys. Implement retry logic with exponential backoff to handle rate limits, typically set at 100 requests per minute for the base tier. Ensure your client supports HTTP/2 for reduced latency."
          }
